rites serialized through shard 0"],[675,"Structure"],[1863,"successful_polls_count: Number of successful polls"],[785,"Summary"],[1635,"Support for multiple data formats"],[577,"Support for multiple streams, topics and partitions"],[578,"Support for multiple transport protocols (QUIC, TCP, WebSocket, HTTP)"],[602,"Support for OpenTelemetry logs & traces + Prometheus metrics"],[1644,"Support for REST catalogs"],[1643,"Support for S3-compatible storage"],[497,"Supported Features"],[558,"Supported languages SDK"],[372,"Supported Schemas"],[1485,"Suppose you want to create a user that can only poll messages from stream 42, with no other access. You would set up their permissions like this:"],[200,"Suppress output"],[1053,"SYS_NICE - required for setting CPU affinity (sched_setaffinity) in the thread-per-core architecture"],[1167,"System"],[908,"SystemClient - ping, stats, snapshot"],[1665,"Table name: users"],[1899,"Table Polling: Incrementally fetch data from PostgreSQL tables"],[1728,"Table Schema"],[1911,"tables: List of tables to monitor (used for polling and to create publications in CDC)"],[1648,"tables: The names of the Iceberg tables you want to statically route Iggy messages to. The name should include the table’s namespace, separated by a dot (.)."],[1686,"Target collection name"],[1682,"Target database name"],[516,"target_format: Target format for conversion (json, proto, text)"],[1748,"target_table: Name of the table to insert messages into"],[867,"TCP"],[872,"TCP"],[894,"TCP"],[989,"TCP"],[1092,"TCP"],[1103,"TCP"],[1145,"TCP"],[892,"TCP (default)"],[1029,"TCP provides the highest performance and throughput as it works directly with the binary data without an additional overhead of e.g. HTTP spec along with the JSON serialization."],[1126,"TCP provides the highest performance as it works directly with binary data without the overhead of HTTP or TLS handshakes (unless TLS is enabled). Key features:"],[197,"TCP server address (default: localhost:8090)"],[666,"